# Next.js — Ops & Architecture (Part 5)

## 29. Security

- Sanitize inputs; validate API responses; prefer httpOnly cookies; CSRF if cookies.
- No secrets in `NEXT_PUBLIC_`; CSP headers; SRI for third-party scripts.

## 30. CI Pipeline

Run: `lint`, `type-check`, `test`, `build`. Add: source maps for Sentry; Dependabot/Renovate; `npm audit`; bundle-size and Lighthouse checks.

## 31. Monitoring

Sentry, LogRocket, Datadog RUM for errors and performance.

## 33. Feature Flags & Analytics

- **Feature flags**: Env vars or remote (LaunchDarkly). Remove when stable.
- **Analytics**: GA4, Plausible. Init in layout; respect consent. Disable in dev via env.

## 34. Additional Patterns

- **next/link**: Use `<Link href>` for internal nav; enables prefetch.
- **URL search params**: `useSearchParams` for filters, shareable links.
- **Breadcrumbs**: Shared component.
- **File upload**: Progress, validation, error handling.
- **Date/number**: `date-fns`, `Intl.NumberFormat`.
- **Print**: `@media print`.
- **Prefetch**: `queryClient.prefetchQuery` on Link hover.

## 35. Deployment & Ops

- **Vercel**: Connect repo; auto-detects Next.js.
- **Docker**: Multi-stage (node build, node/nginx serve).
- **Husky + lint-staged**: Pre-commit lint and format.
- **PWA**: `@ducanh2912/next-pwa` or similar.

## 36. Architecture Philosophy

```
UI → Components
Logic → Hooks
State → Redux
Async → Saga
Server Data → React Query
Validation → Zod
Networking → API Layer
SEO → Metadata API
Performance → Next.js Optimizations
```

One tool, one responsibility.

## Debugging workflow

When fixing bugs: reproduce → root cause → fix → regression test → verify → commit.

| Action | Command |
|--------|---------|
| Run tests | `npm test` |
| Lint | `next lint` or `npm run lint` |
| Type-check | `tsc --noEmit` |
| E2E | `npx playwright test` |
| Commit | `fix(scope): [bug description]` then `test(scope): add regression for [bug]` |

## Checklist

- [ ] Security: no secrets in `NEXT_PUBLIC_`; httpOnly cookies; sanitize inputs; CSP/SRI.
- [ ] CI: lint, type-check, test, build; Dependabot/Renovate; `npm audit`; source maps for Sentry.
- [ ] Feature flags and analytics: env or remote; respect consent; disable in dev.
